==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: jerky
<hw>jerk"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving by
jerks and starts; characterized by abrupt transitions; <as>as, a
<ex>jerky</ex> vehicle; a <ex>jerky</ex> style.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Foolish; ridiculous; stupid.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>jerky</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: jerky
<hw>jerk"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted from Peruv.
<ets>charqui</ets> dried beef.]</ety> <def>Meat, especially beef, that
has been cut in strips and dried; meat that has been jerked; see first
<er>jerk</er>, <pos>v.</pos>; <as>as, beef <ex>jerky</ex></as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jermoonal</ent>⟦br⟧
